abstract="This paper suggests an internet-based tool for cardiac diagnosis in children. The main focus of the paper is the intelligent algorithms for processing heart sounds that are implementable on an internet platform. The algorithms are based on the statistical classification methods, tailored for the heart sound signal processing. The algorithms, applied to 55 healthy and 45 children with congenital heart diseases. The accuracy of the algorithm is estimated to be 86.0Â {\%} in screening the children with pathological murmurs, and 95.7Â {\%}, 92.9Â {\%} and 91.4Â {\%} in detecting the children with aortic stenosis, pulmonary stenosis and mitral regurgitation, respectively, showing an acceptable performance to be employed as a decision support tool.",
