abstract="Object Identifier (OID) has been used in various areas, but its usage has been limited to naming things for a long time. In order to extend OID for identifying Web services, we suggested a new kind of OID named Service OID and its relevant resolution scheme. It is expected for devices to easily collaborate by resolving a simple number-shaped Service OID to the corresponding URI. This simple resolution seems straightforward, but it is not enough for a caller to use the converted URI because every URI needs its unique parameter signature. For this, in the proposed resolution scheme, a data schema was designed and used to provide the binding information of URI.",
